// BizRethink-specific Prisma model additions.
//
// This file is the SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for all custom DB tables added by
// BizRethink on top of Documenso's upstream schema. It is NEVER concatenated
// directly into Prisma's schema by hand — instead, `merge-into-schema.mjs`
// reads this file and appends its contents into `packages/prisma/schema.prisma`
// between marker comments at build time. Running `merge-into-schema.mjs` is
// idempotent: it strips any existing marker block before re-appending.
//
// Wired in via overlay 007 — `packages/prisma/package.json` calls this merge
// script before every `prisma generate`.
//
// Conventions:
//   - All model names are prefixed with `Bizrethink` to avoid collision with
//     any upstream model Documenso may add later.
//   - Encrypted columns use `String` type (not bytes) because we encrypt with
//     `NEXT_PRIVATE_ENCRYPTION_KEY` and store the result as base64.
//   - Foreign-key relations to upstream models (Organisation, User) reference
//     the upstream tables by name. These FKs are added on the upstream side
//     by the merge step (since Prisma requires both ends of a relation to be
//     declared in the same schema). Specifically: when `additions.prisma`
//     declares a relation to `Organisation`, the merge script must also patch
//     `Organisation`'s reverse-relation field. Until that's automated, the
//     reverse-relation field is added manually as a comment in this file and
//     applied via overlay if/when needed.
//
// Empty for now — Phase B/C will populate this with `BizrethinkOrganisationSmtpConfig`
// and `BizrethinkInstanceSigningConfig` models. The merge mechanism is shipped
// first as a prerequisite so the schema additions can be added safely.

// (no models yet — Phase B is the first to add one)
